  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bacterial vaginosis is a common vaginal condition involving a reduction in the amount of
      Lactobacilli, the normal bacteria colonizing the vagina, and an overgrowth of pathogenic
      bacteria. The presence of bacterial vaginosis in pregnancy is associated with an increased
      risk of preterm delivery. After a course of antibiotic treatment, recurrence of bacterial
      vaginosis has been reported in 10-70% of cases. This study aims to verify if administration
      of vaginal Lactobacilli may reduce the occurrence rate after antibiotic treatment of
      bacterial vaginosis during pregnancy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
